  "abstract": "TED-TTS is a training-free framework for intra-utterance emotion and duration control in pretrained zero-shot TTS. It combines segment-aware emotion conditioning with 2D causal masks and Monotonic Stream Alignment, plus segment-aware duration steering with local duration embedding control and global EOS logit modulation. The paper also constructs MED-TTS, a 30,000-sample multi-emotion and duration-annotated text dataset for fine-tuning a Qwen3-8B automatic prompt constructor.",
